Package: rogme
Title: Robust Graphical Methods For Group Comparisons
Version: 0.2.1
Date: 2019-25-02
Authors@R: c(person("Guillaume", "Rousselet", email = "Guillaume.Rousselet@glasgow.ac.uk", role = c("aut", "cre")),
             person("Rand", "Wilcox", email = "rwilcox@usc.edu", role = "aut"))
Maintainer: Guillaume Rousselet <Guillaume.Rousselet@glasgow.ac.uk>
Description: Robust methods to compare and visualise groups of continuous
    variables. Based on Rand Wilcox's shift functions, difference asymmetry
    functions, and tools for quantile estimation. The outputs of these core tools can be visualised using graphical representations based on ggplot2.
Depends:
    R (>= 3.3.2)
Imports:
    dplyr (>= 0.8.0),
    tidyr (>= 0.8.2),
    ggbeeswarm (>= 0.5.3),
    ggplot2 (>= 3.0.0),
    tibble (>= 1.2.0),
    HDInterval (>= 0.2.0),
    tidybayes (>= 1.0.3)
Suggests: 
    knitr,
    testthat,
    rmarkdown
License: MIT + file LICENSE
Language: en-UK
LazyData: TRUE
RoxygenNote: 6.1.1
VignetteBuilder: knitr
Encoding: UTF-8
URL: https://github.com/GRousselet/rogme
BugReports: https://github.com/GRousselet/rogme/issues
